##
## Intent-
##       1) Provide a header library and associated (possibly operating
##          system dependent) implementations.
##       2) Provide implementation examples, some of which are useful.
##       3) Provide implementation examples and tests of operating system
##          and/or library functions.
##       4) Provide implementation examples and tests of C++ functionality.
##       5) Provide associated object library skeletons.
##
##############################################################################
##
## Implementation notes-
##       GNU makefiles are used for all supported implementations.
##       For Windows, this can be accomplished by installing CYGWIN and
##       including C:\CYGWIN\BIN in the %PATH% environment variable.
##
## Operating systems supported (and associated #ifdef controls)-
##       (See ./ctl/. for OS dependent Makefile fragments.)
##       (#define)   (Environment)
##       _OS_BSD     (Either _OS_CYGWIN or _OS_LINUX)
##       _OS_WIN     (Windows (TM))
##       _OS_CYGWIN  (BSD: If uname output contains "CYGWIN")
##       _OS_LINUX   (BSD: If uname output contains "Linux")
##
